August 15, 2018

First case study: "Australian Domestic Tourism"

Data description:

  • 304 quarterly time series (Length of each time series: 228 - 1998~2016)
  • Four hierarchy groups:
  1. State (4 levels - A~G)
  2. Zone (27 levels - AA~GB)
  3. Region (76 levels - AAA~GBD)
  4. Purpose (4 levels - Holiday, Visiting, Business, Other)

Six methods:

  1. Forecasting hierarchical time series using optimal combination reconciliation with arima bottom level forecast
  2. Forecasting hierarchical time series using optimal combination reconciliation with ets bottom level forecast
  3. Forecasting hierarchical time series using optimal combination reconciliation with OLS bottom level forecast
  4. Forecasting time series using arima models
  5. Forecasting time series using ets models
  6. Forecasting time series using OLS models

TourismData: Comparing all methods - with and without hierarchy - mean(log(RMSE))

Method Mean(log(RMSE))
arima 1.585
Hierarchy-arima 1.705
ets 1.594
Hierarchy-ets 1.632
OLS 1.419
Hierarchy-OLS 1.737
